@page "/"
@using Brace.Examples

<PageTitle>Examples of Component State!</PageTitle>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>This demo aims to show how you can utilize the new StatefulBaseComponent and keep values in sync without
            causing other side-effects from within the component.</p>
        <p>
            In the child component:
            - User interactions (typing, clicking, etc.) should invoke the
            EventCallback to notify the parent
            - The change handlers (like OnNameChangedAsync) are for observing when the
            parent sends new values down

            In the parent component:
            - Handle the EventCallback
            - Update your own state
            - Let Blazor pass the updated value back to the child

            This creates the proper two-way data flow that Blazor expects.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

